properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: [4 Mar 1628/1629] King Charles I chartered Mass. Bay Co. to establish a colony stretching from 3 mi. N of the Merrimack R., to 3 mi. S of the Charles R. & extending from the Atlantic to the Pacific. N limit in dispute, only mod. limits of MA mapped.

properties.NAME: New Plymouth Colony
properties.CHANGE: [13 Jan 1629/1630] The Council for New England issued a new land patent (the "Old Charter")  that granted land title and trading rights, but no powers of government, to New Plymouth colony. New Plymouth Colony included part of present Rhode Island.

properties.NAME: Pawtuxet Settlement
properties.CHANGE: In 1642, Massachusetts, responding to a request from disgruntled Rhode Islanders, extended its jurisdiction over the settlement at Pawtuxet.

properties.NAME: NORFOLK (orig)
properties.CHANGE: NORFOLK (original, extinct) created as one of four original Massachusetts counties; included New Hampshire settlements.

properties.NAME: ESSEX
properties.CHANGE: ESSEX created as one of four original counties in Massachusetts.

properties.NAME: MIDDLESEX
properties.CHANGE: MIDDLESEX created as one of four original counties in Massachusetts.

properties.NAME: NCA 1
properties.CHANGE: Non-County Area 1 in Massachusetts colony was unsettled, unorganized area covering the western half of the province.

properties.NAME: SUFFOLK
properties.CHANGE: SUFFOLK created as one of four original counties in Massachusetts. SUFFOLK included territory in the northeast corner of present Rhode Island.

properties.NAME: YORKSHIRE (Me.)
properties.CHANGE: Massachusetts created YORKSHIRE (now YORK, Me.) after southern Maine towns acknowledged Mass. jurisdiction to territory within the boundaries it declared on 26 May 1652. Claim conflicted with 1635 grant of Maine to Ferdinando Gorges.
properties.CITATION: (Farnham, 7:274, 288; Mass. Recs., vol. 4, pt. 1:124; Reid, Maine, 21)

properties.NAME: HAMPSHIRE
properties.CHANGE: HAMPSHIRE created from Non-County Area 1 (towns of Springfield, Northampton, Hadley, and all territory within 30 miles), effectively covering entire western part of the province.

properties.NAME: SUFFOLK
properties.CHANGE: SUFFOLK lost to Rhode Island when the provincial boundary was adjusted after King Charles II granted Rhode Island a charter as a self-governing corporate colony.

properties.NAME: New Plymouth Colony
properties.CHANGE: New Plymouth Colony lost to Rhode Island when King Charles II granted Rhode Island a charter as a self-governing corporate colony.

properties.NAME: SUFFOLK
properties.CHANGE: [May 1664] SUFFOLK lost to the New Plymouth Colony when a joint commission from Massachusetts and Plymouth demarcated their mutual boundary ("Old Colony Line").

properties.NAME: New Plymouth Colony
properties.CHANGE: [May 1664] New Plymouth Colony gained from SUFFOLK and Rhode Island Colony when a joint commission from Massachusetts and Plymouth demarcated their mutual boundary ("Old Colony Line").

properties.NAME: SUFFOLK
properties.CHANGE: [27 Feb 1664/1665] SUFFOLK gained from Rhode Island Colony when royal commissioners set the provincial boundaries of Mass., New Plymouth, and R.I. along the Blackstone River and the east side of Narragansett Bay, pending conclusive royal decision.

properties.NAME: New Plymouth Colony
properties.CHANGE: [27 February 1664/1665] New Plymouth gained from Rhode Island Colony when royal boundary commissioners set Rhode Island's eastern limit along the Blackstone River and east coast of Narragansett Bay, pending a conclusive royal decision.

properties.NAME: YORK (Me.)
properties.CHANGE: YORK (Me., formerly called YORKSHIRE) was reinstated when Massachusetts reasserted authority over all of Maine west of the Kennebec R., an area that had been put under royal government in June 1665.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts Claim
properties.CHANGE: Massachusetts reasserted authority over all of Maine west of the Kennebec R., an area that had been put under royal government in June 1665.

properties.NAME: HAMPSHIRE
properties.CHANGE: HAMPSHIRE gained from non-county area in Connecticut when the town of Westfield (now Southwick) was created from the town of Springfield. Part of Westfield extended into Connecticut, the result of disagreement over the line between the two colonies.

properties.NAME: DEVONSHIRE (ext)
properties.CHANGE: By 7 October 1673, Massachusetts claimed some of the Duke of York's territory in present Maine and created DEVONSHIRE (extinct). County was unnamed until 27 May 1674.

properties.NAME: HAMPSHIRE
properties.CHANGE: HAMPSHIRE gained non-county area in Connecticut when the town of Suffield was created. Suffield was entirely within present Connecticut, the result of uncertain geographical knowledge and disagreement over the boundary between the colonies.

properties.NAME: ESSEX
properties.CHANGE: ESSEX gained towns of Amesbury, Haverhill, and Salisbury from NORFOLK (original) when King Charles II made New Hampshire a royal colony separate from Massachusetts; NORFOLK (original) eliminated.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts Claim
properties.CHANGE: [17 Mar 1679/1680] YORK (Me.) eliminated when Massachusetts organized a new government for Maine (area between the Piscataqua and Kennebec Rivers) in accordance with terms of Ferdinando Gorges's 1635 grant.

properties.NAME: HAMPSHIRE
properties.CHANGE: HAMPSHIRE gained non-county area in Connecticut when town of Enfield was created. Most of Enfield was in present Connecticut, the result of uncertain geographical knowledge and disagreement over the boundary between the colonies.

properties.NAME: DUKES (N.Y.)
properties.CHANGE: DUKES (N.Y., extinct) created by New York, in present Massachusetts, from Elizabeth Islands, Martha's Vineyard, and Nantucket.

properties.NAME: BARNSTABLE
properties.CHANGE: BARNSTABLE created as one of three original counties in New Plymouth Colony.

properties.NAME: PLYMOUTH
properties.CHANGE: PLYMOUTH created as one of three original counties in New Plymouth Colony.

properties.NAME: BRISTOL
properties.CHANGE: BRISTOL created as one of three original counties in New Plymouth Colony.

properties.NAME: SUFFOLK
properties.CHANGE: [15 Mar 1689/1690] SUFFOLK gained non-county area in Conn. when Mass. created the town of Woodstock. Woodstock lay almost entirely within present Conn., the result of uncertain geographical knowledge and disagreement over the line bet. the two colonies.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: King William III  & Queen Mary II issued a new charter for the province of Mass. Bay, extending boundaries to encompass New Plymouth Colony, Nantucket, Martha's Vineyard; and territory in present Maine. Map depicts non-county area in Mass. Bay Colony.
properties.CITATION: (Mass. Col. Acts, vol. 1, ch. 27 [1692-1693], sec. 1/p. 63; Swindler, 5:80)

properties.NAME: YORK (Me.)

properties.CITATION: (Mass. Col. Acts, vol. 1, ch. 27 [1692-1693], sec. 1/p. 63; Swindler, 5:80)
